  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Repurposed development funding for Ebola response (Mitigating the spread of Ebola through community awareness raising)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of this project is to raise social awareness on Ebola and how to mitigate transmition in the Lofa and Monteserrado Districts in Liberia.  The response focuces on prevention, with most activities supporting the Communication Pillar. Activities include: distribution of Communication and Education (IEC) materials to promote public awareness,  training health worker in contact tracing, stakeholder training in Ebola messaging. In addition to the communication component,  other activities include installation of hand washing stations, distribution of personal protective equipment (PPE) kits to health facilities and isolation units support to burial and ambulance teams and response coordination.</narrative>
  </description>
